  <description>
    <p>
      Jellyfin is the volunteer-built media solution that puts you in control
      of your media. Stream to any device from your own server, with no
      strings attached. Your media, your server, your way.
    </p>
    <p>About this Flatpak:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        It includes both the server and a web-based graphical user interface.
      </li>
      <li>
        The web GUI will automatically open in your browser about 10 seconds after you start the app.
      </li>
      <li>
        For more information check the Help and FAQ links below.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <!-- TODO: Move to FAQ -->
    <p>
      NOTE: HDR Tone mapping on Intel extension
    </p>
    <p><code>flatpak install flathub org.jellyfin.JellyfinServer.Plugin.IntelComputeRuntime</code></p>
    <p>
      Create media folders
    </p>
    <p><code>mkdir -p "${HOME}/Jellyfin Server Media/"{Movies,Music,Shows,Books,Photos}</code></p>
    <p>
      Open Jellyfin Data
    </p>
    <p><code>xdg-open ~/.var/app/org.jellyfin.JellyfinServer</code></p>
    <p>
      Raspberry Pi 4 GPU
    </p>
    <p><code>flatpak override --user --device=all org.jellyfin.JellyfinServer</code></p>
  </description>

